    <note>Chao(2) Gongzan [13548] In 1128, Chao(2) Yuezhi [3029] told Gongzan that he was young and should devote his efforts to reading books. He should first (i.e. the beginning of his education should be to) read the five classics, the Han Yu, Sima Qian, Gongyang commentary and the Chunqiu. This is the sequence of reading books. I give him the address of Yuezhi in ca. 1128. CBD, 3, 1949.</note>
